### Employee CRUD API Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:5000

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/

###

### 2. Create Employee
POST http://localhost:5000/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "position": "Software Engineer",
  "salary": 75000
}

###

### 3. Create Another Employee
POST http://localhost:5000/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Jane",
  "last_name": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "position": "Product Manager",
  "salary": 85000
}

###

### 4. Get All Employees
GET http://localhost:5000/api/employees

###

### 5. Get Single Employee (change ID as needed)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/employees/1

###

### 6. Update Employee (change ID as needed)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/employees/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "position": "Senior Software Engineer",
  "salary": 95000
}

###

### 7. Delete Employee (change ID as needed)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/employees/1

###
